  "prompt": "Were humans around during the existence of dinosaur?",
  "response": "No, humans were not around during the existence of dinosaurs. Dinosaurs first appeared during the Triassic period, approximately 230 million years ago, and they became the dominant terrestrial vertebrates until their extinction about 66 million years ago at the end of the Cretaceous period. \n\nModern humans (Homo sapiens) evolved much later, with the earliest known fossils dated to around 300,000 years ago. Therefore, there is a vast time gap, approximately 65 million years, between the extinction of dinosaurs and the emergence of humans.",
